API URL

Example:

https://myproject.replit.app/start

When Voiceflow sends a request:

GET /start

Your Python server responds.

Example Flask code:

@app.route("/start")
def start():
    return {
        "message": "Hello! How can I help you?"
    }

Voiceflow receives that response.

Headers

Headers carry additional information.

Example:

Authorization

Content-Type

API-Key

If your API requires authentication, the key is passed here.

Parameters

Parameters are the data sent with the request.

Example:

Name = Rahul

Age = 30

Question = "What is AI?"

Voiceflow sends those values to your API.

